<br>
Each side can be seen as right using 100% valid logic.<br>
<br>
Each side can also be seen as wrong using 100% valid logic.<br>
<br>
The hatred is so strong in Israel that there will not be peace there in any of our lifetimes, unless one side wipes the other out. <br>
<br>
Sadly, thats exactly what is going to happen, and it's going to happen slowly. Anyone who thinks any of the violence in that area is new needs a serious history lesson. The area between Egypt and Turkey has been the site of more wars and more bloodshed than anywhere in the world. The current fighting has been going on for most of the last century and only got worse in 1948.<br>
<br>
There have been brief periods of relative calm, but even these are filled with small skirmishes and one faction fighting the other. <br>
<br>
The biggest problem is that both sides have a valid claim to the same land and peaceful coexistance is not an option. And since Neither side is willing to leave their god-given holy land, the only result can be war.<br>
<br>
As I mentioned before. Its a war. It will be a war for a long time to come. A long slow war with long drawn out periods of terror, blood and death for all involved.<br>
<br>
The only true way to obtain peace in such a situation is Armed Occupation by a third, neutral party. The occupation would have to last three generations, long enough for those who feel the hate now to die. Unfortuneatly no political body is willing to commit to such a long occupation. Modern attempts at occupying territory to enforce coexistance between factions all fail because the peacekeepers are called home too soon. <br>
<br>
History has shown us that occupation does work to bring a population into harmonious coexistance. However the last time this has been a documented success would be the Holy Roman Empire. Prior to that the Romans understood the need for long term military occupation. Sadly the only such occupation that currently exists in a state that could remotely be called a success would be the Taliban in Afganistan...but that is a different story. It might be important to note that in every successful case the occupied land became part of the occupier's nation or the occupying force took over the local government. I don't see that happening in Israel.<br>
<br>
The only way other than armed occupation for the Palestines and the Israelis to come together in peace would be to provide both of them with an even more despicable Enemy. This could bring the two factions together very rapidly. Historical examples would be Scotland unifying against England. <br>
<br>
If the US really wanted to help the Israelis and the Palestinians get along we would invade them with obvious intent to conquer and assimilate, making our nation appear as the evil oppressor. But that would backfire, I am sure and while we would certainly bring Israel together as one nation, we would get the rest of the world against us.<br>
<br>
I guess the bottom line is Israel is just a bad place to be right now and doesn't look like it will be getting better any time soon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#E9D756>- </font><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr>Erollisi Marr, The Queen of Love</a><font color=#E9D756> - </font><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18>America Under Attack</a> <font color=#E9D756> - </font> <br>
